    base:desc "Model fidelity is assessed experimentally by comparing predicted temperature trajectories against the measured sensor data. The four‑parameter model demonstrated higher fidelity in reproducing the heat‑bed’s thermal inertia, and therefore was selected for further DT development. Validation consists of running the simulation with the calibrated parameters and quantifying prediction error. Uncertainty arises from sensor noise, unmodelled environmental influences, and parameter estimation error; the DT mitigates these through calibration algorithms that continuously update model parameters. Quality assurance is provided by the monitoring component that flags deviations beyond acceptable error thresholds."
]
